com.camerontec.catalys.util.text.table

Class TableSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.text.table.TableSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class TableSet
extends Object
implements Serializable
    TableSet groups together a set of Tables. When ever a new header is added a new table is automatically created. To make the table set both platform and language independent a TableSet has it's own encode/decode methods which convert a TableSet to and from an ASCII string.

    The ASCII encoding follows these rules:

    Each Row begins with the row type either ACK, NACK or HEADER(SOH)

    Each columns is separated by an ETX character.

    E.G:

    [SOH]Header1[ETX]Header2[ETX]Header3[ETX]

    [ACK]Data1[ETX]Data2[ETX]

    [NACK]Some bad data[ETX]
